## Open questions

| # | Item | Owner | Blocks build? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Q1 | **E4 question set** — fixes the final endpoint/tool list and the coverage matrix (C6). | VP Data (spec §6) | **Yes — final surface.** B1 query-core scaffolding can start against the provisional contract. |
| Q2 | **Frozen gold contract** — A's per-mart `schema.yml` (C3). B1 binds to it; until committed, B's column list is provisional. | Component A | **Yes — B1 functions** can't be finalized without it. |
| Q3 | **`_gold_run_id` publish mechanism** — A must emit it for B's atomic-generation read (C5). | Component A | **Yes — `/freshness` consistency** + cross-endpoint coherence. |
| Q4 | **FastAPI + MCP split risk** — held as one component (shared B1); revisit only if MCP needs logic HTTP doesn't. | Us | No — default holds. |

**Accepted risks (recorded, not fixed):**
- **E2/E1 are inherited, not independently measured here** — serving does lookup
  over pre-aggregated gold (E2 mechanism) and is read-only/gold-only (E1 by
  construction). The literal latency/availability KPIs are production
  measurements out of this repo's scope. Owner: CTO; reason: §3 out-of-scope.

## Spec traceability

- **E4** (self-serve, no new report) — B3 MCP tools + B2 endpoints *are* the
  self-serve surface, one per frozen question.
- **E2** (queries <5s) — inherited: serving does lookup over pre-aggregated gold,
  no heavy scan at request time.
- **E3** (freshness) — `/freshness` + `freshness` tool expose
  `gold_freshness.lag_seconds` as the observable instrument.
- **E1** (isolation) — read-only, gold-only, by construction; proven by the
  isolation test.
